"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"703286",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Symptoms and Signs"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"50aa46",
"children":[
"Look for symptoms suggesting hypothyroidism:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b7506b",
"children":[
"weakness, lethargy, fatigue"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f9f3fa",
"children":[
"depression, impaired concentration"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a9f804",
"children":[
"myalgia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c02595",
"children":[
"cold intolerance"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"940959",
"children":[
"constipation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"87d866",
"children":[
"weight gain"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"343ebf",
"children":[
"menstrual irregularity or menorrhagia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d434d8",
"children":[
"carpal tunnel syndrome"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d95a99",
"children":[
"Look for signs suggesting hypothyroidism:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bbeaa0",
"children":[
"bradycardia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"31054e",
"children":[
"hypothermia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8c8c43",
"children":[
"goiter"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bcf62a",
"children":[
"cool dry skin"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ff0d9a",
"children":[
"delayed deep tendon reflex relaxation phase"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"651583",
"children":[
"myopathy"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"182bf7",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Causes"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e3b6cb",
"children":[
"The most common causes of hypothyroidism include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"69cf74",
"children":[
"chronic lymphocytic (Hashimoto) thyroiditis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0ee3cb",
"children":[
"thyroidectomy"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5edf3e",
"children":[
"previous radioactive iodine ablation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7e0613",
"children":[
"history of external beam radiation to the neck"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4c7c0c",
"children":[
"Transient mild hypothyroidism typically occurs during the second phase of ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"destructive thyroiditis"
]
},
" (initial phase is hyperthyroidism). Permanent hypothyroidism may follow either postpartum thyroiditis (more common) or subacute thyroiditis (less common)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8d407e",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Medication-induced hypothyroidism"
]
},
" can occur with the use of certain drugs, including lithium carbonate, interferon alfa, interleukin-2, and amiodarone."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1ccaef",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Central hypothyroidism"
]
},
" results from pituitary disease or from previous surgery or radiation therapy to the sella. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"thyroid-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"TSH"
]
},
" and free ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"free thyroxine",
"children":[
"T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"4"
]
}
]
},
" are suppressed."
]
}
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s11_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"812c01",
"children":[
"Order TSH and free T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"4"
]
},
" to make the diagnosis. Measurement of T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"3"
]
},
" levels is generally not necessary. An antithyroid peroxidase antibody assay is associated with Hashimoto thyroiditis but is not needed to make the diagnosis; high levels are associated with an increased risk of permanent hypothyroidism."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"28bfef",
"children":[
"Hypothyroidism may be associated with hyperprolactinemia; hyponatremia; and increased ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"creatine kinase",
"children":[
"CK"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"aspartate aminotransferase",
"children":[
"AST"
]
},
","
]
},
" and cholesterol levels."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d027c8",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Nonthyroidal illness syndrome"
]
},
" occurs in patients who are acutely ill with a nonthyroidal illness. Testing reveals low or normal free T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"4"
]
},
" and suppressed TSH (initially), followed by elevated TSH (recovery phase). Normalization of thyroid function tests occurs 4 to 8 weeks after recovery."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"553d2f",
"children":[
"Thyroid scan and radioactive iodine uptake tests are not used to make the diagnosis of hypothyroidism."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_en_s11_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s11_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"983f9f",
"children":[
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Levothyroxine is used to treat hypothyroidism."
]
},
" Treatment of subclinical hypothyroidism is controversial. Most guidelines support these treatment indications for subclinical hypothyroidism (TSH >10 μU/mL):"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"aa7c04",
"children":[
"symptomatic"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"42c70b",
"children":[
"pregnant or planning to become pregnant"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ccea48",
"children":[
"possibly age <30 years"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"11dbd0",
"children":[
"Levothyroxine should be taken on an empty stomach 60 minutes before consuming breakfast or coffee. Recall that celiac disease, calcium and iron supplements, and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" can decrease levothyroxine absorption; medications affecting absorption should be taken at least 4 hours apart from levothyroxine."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"73c13f",
"children":[
"No treatment is required for nonthyroidal illness syndrome."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a0776e",
"children":[
"Check thyroid function tests frequently during pregnancy in women with a known diagnosis of hypothyroidism taking thyroxine, because maternal thyroxine demand increases by 30% to 50%."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_en_s11_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
}
]
},
